Durban - The KwaZulu-Natal Department of Education has had its hands full this past month as it navigated one crisis after another. If teachers were not issuing corporal punishment to children, they were allegedly calling them monkeys. The power of social media has played a pivotal role with many of the incidents being captured by pupils themselves on their smartphones. Here is a recap of some the issues that have made headlines this month Assegai Primary School To view this video please enable JavaScript, and consider upgrading to a web browser that
